Summary of Key Decision Rationales
•	Jia Hui was selected as the main persona because she makes the final decisions about hiring, payroll, workload, and deadlines.
•	The main issue is the conflict between employee well-being and business survival.
•	Financial pressure was selected as the central theme because it affects most of her decisions.
Takeaways from Empathy Stage
•	Startup employment decisions are both financial and emotional.
•	Overtime may help meet a deadline, but it can cause burnout and more mistakes later.
•	Founders need simple tools to manage payroll, staffing costs, workload, and employee feedback.
Potential Biases or Assumptions
•	The interview only represents one startup founder.
•	Employee opinions were not directly collected.
•	Some answers may describe extreme situations rather than normal daily work.
2.7 Review of Empathy Process
The interview and empathy map were useful because they revealed Jia Hui’s financial pressure, emotional stress, and responsibility for her employees. The questions helped identify important problems such as high hiring costs, employee burnout, limited cash flow, and investor pressure. However, the research only focused on one founder, so it may not represent every startup. The process could be improved by interviewing employees, other startup founders, HR professionals, and investors. Future interviews should also use more follow-up questions and ask participants to rank their most serious problems.

